{
  "title": "test_2",
  "description": "This space provides a synthetic sample of healthcare claims data, enabling educational and exploratory analysis of patient demographics, diagnoses, procedures, provider details, and claim financials.\n\n**Capabilities:**\n- Analyze patterns in medical and pharmacy claims, such as common diagnoses, procedures, and service utilization.\n- Segment claims by patient demographics (age, gender, geography) or provider information.\n- Examine claim types (professional vs. institutional), service dates, and payer types.\n- Evaluate financial metrics including line charges and allowed amounts.\n- Explore provider networks through National Provider Identifiers (NPIs) and taxonomy codes.\n\n**Limitations:**\n- Data is synthetic and intended only for non-production, educational use\u2014results do not reflect real patient or provider behavior.\n- The dataset is limited in size (1,500+ patients) and does not cover all healthcare scenarios.\n- Not suitable for commercial, regulatory reporting, or patient-level decision-making.\n- Does not contain actual patient identifiers or allow access to broader HealthVerity data; for real-world or project-specific data, contact HealthVerity at [https://www.healthverity.com/contact/](https://www.healthverity.com/contact/).",
